cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a deep learning approach for estimating pharmacokinetic parameters from DCE-MRI data. The approach involves designing a custom loss function that incorporates a forward physical model, which relates the PK parameters to corrupted image-time series obtained due to subsampling in k-space. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it involves image analysis and restoration. Additionally, the use of deep learning models and loss functions suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The incorporation of a physical model in the loss function suggests that it may also belong to the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of MRI data suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
